      "date": "2012-10-17 06:42:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(8 inline comments)\n\nExcept for some redundant code, I more worry about whether the new global atomic/mutex variables will much affect the performance or not. According to the experience from Liang's SMP project, it is better to avoid global contention. It is not a string reason to deny the patch, but please think carefully when you use them.",
